						<div class="postbody">So what is the best, using direct communication with VGA card, or using the ncurses library ?<br /><br />If the latter, how do we to reprogram character set with the ncurses library so set your own tiles ?<br /><br />If the former, how do I access the VGA card (or it's simulation) with the C language ?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Characters can be anywhere from 1 to 64 scanlines tall. There is a register that controls that, too. (port 3C4h function 9)</div><br />The idea of 1 line characters is interesting, that way we get tiles horizontally and bitmap vertically. However with monochrome 8-piexl wide characters it doesn't make much sense since you can get basically bitmap using 256 characters.<br /><br />The idea of super-tall characters is interesting as well, although I can't think of any usage right now.</div>

